  "text": "We should be careful to mention the current limitations of our work, each of which may provide fruitful ground for future research. First, we study the setting of episodic, finite horizon MDPs and not the more general setting of weakly communicating systems [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Also we assume that the horizon length H is known to the learner. Further, our bounds only improve over previous scaling O(HS √ AT ) for T > H 3 S 3 A. We hope that this work will serve to elucidate several of the existing shortcomings of exploration in the tabular setting and help further the direction of research towards provably optimal exploration in reinforcement learning.",
